Full Description:
Overview:

Fred Hutchinson Cancer Center is an independent, nonprofit organization providing adult cancer treatment and groundbreaking research focused on cancer and infectious diseases. Based in Seattle, Fred Hutch is the only National Cancer Institute-designated cancer center in Washington.
With a track record of global leadership in bone marrow transplantation, HIV/AIDS prevention, immunotherapy and COVID-19 vaccines, Fred Hutch has earned a reputation as one of the world’s leading cancer, infectious disease and biomedical research centers. Fred Hutch operates eight clinical care sites that provide medical oncology, infusion, radiation, proton therapy and related services, and network affiliations with hospitals in five states. Together, our fully integrated research and clinical care teams seek to discover new cures to the world’s deadliest diseases and make life beyond cancer a reality.
At Fred Hutch we value collaboration, compassion, determination, excellence, innovation, integrity and respect. These values are grounded in and expressed through the principles of diversity, equity and inclusion. Our mission is directly tied to the humanity, dignity and inherent value of each employee, patient, community member and supporter. Our commitment to learning across our differences and similarities make us stronger. We seek employees who bring different and innovative ways of seeing the world and solving problems. Fred Hutch is in pursuit of becoming an anti-racist organization. We are committed to ensuring that all candidates hired share our commitment to diversity, anti-racism and inclusion.
Working under supervision and in collaboration with the Comprehensive Center for the Advancement of Scientific Strategies (COMPASS) consortium coordination and data management ream, the Data Analyst will utilize data analysis and reporting skills and tools to create reporting artifacts in support of data quality, reporting and analysis needs. Reporting products will include, but not limited to, simple reports, complex reports, dashboards, analytic data sets, data visualizations and data mining constructs in support of COMPASS’ study coordination and data management efforts which support discovery and validation of biomarkers through translational and observational clinical trials at the Fred Hutchinson Cancer Center.
Responsibilities:
Gathering and documenting requirements from the study and coordination team and then translating those requirements into an analytics solution that meets each study’s reporting needs.
Possess knowledge on a wide range of possible reporting solutions and have sufficient discernment skills to select the most appropriate solution for each set of requirements.
Prepare for and actively participate in design and development reviews.
Will serve as a liaison with the study coordination and biostatics team around the usage and deployment of reporting solutions and tools.
Will understand reporting using SQL relational database stored source data.
Develop data and reporting solutions for ad hoc data requests that involves new metrics or are not well defined or are considered advanced data requests
Assist the data quality team in tracking down/debugging potential data quality issues.
Prepare documentation for deployment purposes and respond to any implementation issues as needed to ensure quality deliverables have been met.
Qualifications:

MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS:
Bachelor’s degree with a major in statistics, biostatistics, public health, or other field with data manipulation experience
Minimum of 2 years professional database reporting development experience with statistical and data visualization software (SAS, R, Tableau Software, Power BI etc.)
Knowledge of relational databases and SQL
Knowledge of basic statistics and experience working with statistical data
Sharp analytical abilities, proven design skills and problem-solving skills
Strong organizational skills, ability to multi-task, self-motivation, and flexibility
Capable to work both independently and in a team environment
Ability to communicate clearly and concisely both orally and in writing
Enjoys working in a team environment and has a proven record of positive contributions to the work of the team
Demonstrated experience promoting a diverse, inclusive, and respectful workplace.
PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS:

Full Description:
The Business Analyst is responsible for reviewing, prioritizing, modifying and recommending business requirements applied to our databases and systems under the direct oversight of the Business Process Director. In addition, this role will pinpoint how Exotic can leverage its strengths and improve its weaknesses through various business process improvements and through the use of technology or software. This role works closely with the programming team to test the solution, record and track technical issues and implement any needed changes.

Duties and Responsibilities:

Review, prioritize and propose business process improvements across all departments within the organization.

Recommend solutions that are right sized, robust, stable and designed for the long term. Must be able to see big picture impacts on other systems and assess risk.

Partner with business/user representatives to understand the customer processes and user needs.

Develop business processes using task flow analysis and work flow analysis

 Research, analyze, and present the most relevant information about the project

 Know when to recommend a project be delayed or terminated

Able to differentiate between desired and required user needs

Use strong analytical reasoning to understand end user’s requirements to create an operational application.

Acquire deep working knowledge of Exotic’s business systems and bring efficient and effective changes for better performance.

Understand the technical designs and specifications.

Communicate effectively with internal teams and external clients to understand their needs and deliver both functional requirements and formal, documented business processes.

Act as project manager for cross functional team initiatives.


Required Skills

Required Experience
The ideal candidate will have excellent written, oral, organization, project management, presentation and interpersonal communication skills. Because business analysts must interact with executives, users and technical staff, networking and team building skills are preferred. Business analysts should also have the ability to train, lead and mentor other analysts.

Time and project management and prioritization skills a must. Demonstrated success in leading projects to close on time, within budget and within scope. Able to understand the customer’s needs and position a solution which best addresses all of the customer’s needs.

Strong analytic and technical skills including writing functional and technical requirements. Database design, software design and testing methodology a must.

Strong problem solving and decision making skills.

Full Description:
JOB DESCRIPTION – Senior Business Analyst
Title: Senior Business Analyst
Job Function: Product
Role Type: Full time
Location: Bellevue, WA
Reporting to: Chief Product Officer
Stakeholders: Product / IT
About Resulticks
Resulticks is a fully integrated, real-time marketing automation platform designed to help brands worldwide reach, acquire, and retain satisﬁed customers. Built from the ground up by experts in marketing, technology, and business management, Resulticks enables brands to make a transformational leap to conversion-driven, growth-focused personalized engagement. With an advanced CDP at its core. Resulticks offers AI-powered omnichannel orchestration, complete analytics, next-best engagement, attribution at the segment-of-one level, and the world’s first marketing block chain.
Resulticks has been named to the Gartner’s Magic Quadrant 2022 for Multichannel Marketing Hubs for six years in a row and has been awarded with the Microsoft “Elevating Customer Experience with AI” award.
Headquartered in Singapore and New York City, Resulticks is one of the top global martech solutions servicing both B2B/B2B2C and B2C segments. Resulticks’ global presence includes the United States, India, Singapore, Indonesia, Malaysia, Vietnam, Thailand, and the Philippines.
Watch video on RESULTICKS - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=G_OwGy6unP8
Candidate Profile
Resulticks seeks optimistic, high-energy industry veterans with entrepreneurial spirits and proven track records of successful problem-solving and process analysis to join our team as a Senior Business Analyst.
The Senior Business Analyst will be expected to bring subject matter expertise along with experience of solving complex organization information problems. You must have the ability to communicate with members from different teams at different levels of the organization.
The ideal candidate will be a natural collaborator with the ability to develop and monitor new computer programs to ensure business requirements are being met. You should have strong analytical skills and be detail-oriented in order to provide the best solutions to current business processes.
Key Responsibilities
Create and maintain project schedules by developing project plans and specifications, estimating time and resources, monitoring milestone completion, tracking all phase of the project lifecycle, providing timely reporting of issues that impact project progress, coordinating actions and resolving conflicts
Determine operational objectives, evaluating output requirements and formats.
Design new computer programs after analyzing requirements and constructing workflow charts and diagrams.
Improve current systems by identifying problems and designing modifications.
Support and align efforts to meet customer and business needs.
Define project requirements and details which includes identifying project milestones, phases, and elements, forming the project team, and creating the project budget.
Monitor project progress by regularly tracking activities, solving any issues along the way and publishing progress reports.
Maintain system protocols by writing and updating procedures.
Write and maintain user documentation, train user, and provide help desk support.
Maintain confidence and protect operations by keeping information confidential.
Prepare technical reports by collecting, analyzing, and summarizing information and trends.
Establish professional networks and participate in professional societies.
Pre-Requisites
Must have 5-10 years of experience in a relevant field.
Strong skills in software design and development along with software documentation and requirements.
Must have the ability to analyze problems and find solutions.
Must have a proven track record of achieving team targets and accomplishing results.
Phenomenal communication, presentation & negotiation skills.
Strong problem-solving and team collaborative skills.
Desirable Skills
Knowledge of Microsoft Visio and Access is advantageous
Expert or intermediate Microsoft 365 skills.
Ability to handle multiple projects in a fast-paced environment
Experience and Academic Qualifications
At minimum, a B.A. or B.S. in a relevant field of study.
Advanced degree or MBA is a plus.
Must have authorization to work in the United States.

Full Description:
Position Description
Seattle Human Resources endeavors to promote an equitable and engaging work environment so employees can do their best work and make a difference for the people and communities we serve. The Department focuses on providing high quality services to all City employees and departments and works collaboratively with department leaders to align policies, practices, and programs citywide to fulfill the vision of workforce equity and excellence.
As part of this mission, the Fire and Police Exams Unit is responsible for developing and administering merit-based, entry-level, and promotional exams under the direction of the Public Safety Civil Service Commission (PSCSC) and on behalf of the Seattle Police and Fire Departments to establish eligibility lists to fill entry-level, lateral, and promotional positions. We strive to administer exams that are equitable, compliant, and transparent. To support these goals, we are looking for a Fire and Police Exams Analyst who will provide program coordination, research and analysis, and support a high volume of exams administered on behalf of the Fire and Police Departments. This position will also increase the unit’s capacity to administer entry and lateral police officer exam administrations.
This position will give you the opportunity to work with a diverse team that centers equity, learning, transparency, and continuous improvement to serve our uniformed employees and the broader community. In this role, you will support the administration of entry and promotional exams, research best practices, analyze data, provide customer service to candidates and partner departments, manage dashboards, budgets, contracts, and records, coordinate public disclosure requests, and provide general logistical support. In addition, you will have the opportunity to regularly utilize your problem-solving and organizational skills to improve exam administration for both the Fire and Police Departments, ultimately making our community a safer and more equitable place by contributing to hiring and promotional processes.
Job Responsibilities
In this role:
You will be successful if you feel passionate about:
Improving administrative processes and identifying opportunities that make a significant impact
Providing exceptional and welcoming customer service to fire and police exam candidates
Solving complex problems creatively and efficiently
Building and maintaining positive team relationships
Maintaining the utmost level of security and confidentiality
Identifying and undoing inequities in examination processes
Utilizing your organizational skills for seamless project coordination and records management
 Your effectiveness will depend on your ability to:
Communicate effectively, both orally and in writing
Apply critical thinking and problem-solving in a fast-paced environment
Research and analyze exam administration decisions, past practices, and best practices, providing recommendations and revisions as necessary
Partner tactfully, courteously, and effectively with a variety of people, members of the Seattle Police and Fire Departments, as well as the Public Safety Civil Service Commission and consultants and other industry subject matter experts
Support Senior Analysts by facilitating exam development committee meetings, administering protest periods, and fielding stakeholder communications
Supporting the Fire & Police Exams Unit in testifying and defending work before the PSCSC
 You will feel prepared if you have experience in:
Supporting and administering employment-related examinations (written, oral board, working tests, practical exams, certifications, etcetera), particularly public safety or apprenticeship exams
Researching and interpreting rules, regulations, contracts, and policies and procedures
Communicating technical exam-related concepts to non-technical audiences
Coordinating exam logistics, such as booking hotels, event spaces, airfare, and shuttles
Applying your advanced skills in Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Outlook
Conducting statistical reports and creating data dashboards
Processing and monitoring contracts and receipts
Providing instructions and assistance to large groups of people
Industrial or Organizational Psychology and Personnel Selection
Qualifications
In addition to the ability to perform the tasks described above, you will need to possess the below required qualifications:
A Bachelor’s Degree in Human Resource Management, Business or Public Administration, Social Sciences, or a related field
Two years in personnel selection assessments (preferably for Civil Service positions), public-sector exams, or performing other human resources-related tasks, or a related field
OR
An Associate Degree in Human Resource Management, Business or Public Administration, Social Sciences, or a related field
Three years in personnel selection assessments (preferably for Civil Service positions), public-sector exams, or performing other human resources-related tasks, or a related field
OR
Four years in personnel selection assessments (preferably for Civil Service positions), public-sector exams, or performing other human resources-related tasks, or a related field
Additional Information
This position is classified a Personnel Analyst and requires the ability to lift 30 pounds and work paid overtime, evenings, and weekends.
The first round of interviews for this position are tentatively scheduled for Thursday, January 12 and Friday, January 13, with the second round taking place on Thursday, January 19, 2023.
Applicants must successfully pass a background check, which will be conducted in accordance with Seattle’s Fair Chance Employment Ordinance, SMC 14.17. Applicants will be given a chance to explain or correct background information and provide verifiable information of good conduct and rehabilitation.
The City of Seattle recognizes every City employee must play a role in ending institutional and structural racism. Our culture is the result of our behavior, our personal commitments, and the ways we courageously share our perspectives and encourage others to do the same. To cultivate an antiracist culture, we seek employees who will engage in the Race and Social Justice Initiative by working to dismantle racist policies and procedures, unlearn the way things have always been done, and provide equitable processes and services.
COVID 19 Vaccination Mandate - City of Seattle employees are required to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19. If hired, you will be required to submit proof of vaccination prior to your employment start date. People are considered fully vaccinated two weeks after their second dose in a two-dose series or two weeks after a single-dose vaccine. Employees may make requests for a reasonable accommodation based on a medical disability or for sincerely held religious beliefs. Philosophical, political, scientific, or sociological objections to vaccination will not be considered for an exemption or accommodation.
APPLICATION PROCESS:
To be considered for this position, please submit your complete application, resume, and cover letter to https://www.governmentjobs.com/careers/seattle no later than 4:00pm Pacific Time on Tuesday, January 3, 2023. In your 1-page cover letter, please explain your interest in this position and identify specifically how the combination of your knowledge, skills, and interests align with our business needs and will contribute to your success in this role. This position is open to all candidates that meet the minimum qualifications. The City of Seattle values diverse perspectives and life experiences. Applicants will be considered regardless of race, color, creed, national origin, ancestry, sex, marital status, disability, religious or political affiliation, age, sexual orientation, medical condition, or pregnancy. The City of Seattle encourages people of all backgrounds to apply, including people of color, immigrants, refugees, women, LGBTQ, people with disabilities, veterans, and those with diverse life experiences. If you have questions, please contact Lindsey King at Lindsey.King@seattle.gov.

Full Description:
Junior Data Strategy Analyst (JDSA)
In support of the Naval Sea Systems Command (NAVSEA) and the Shipboard Maintenance Performance Group (SMPG), the JDSA will help bring cutting edge data analytics to the Navy fleet. Positions are located in Norfolk, VA, and Bremerton, WA.

Roles & Responsibilities:
The Junior Data Strategy Analyst reports to and assist the program’s Senior Data Strategy Analyst (SDSA) in all activities required to modernize the management and analysis of data within the Ship Maintenance Community. The roles and responsibilities of the JDSA will be similar in nature to those of the SDSA but at a level commensurate with the knowledge and experience of the candidate. These include:
Assist in the stand-up (both technical and functional) of the Data Analytics Lab located at SMPG offices, recommend software/hardware analytics and data management toolsets, and recommend functional responsibilities for the other SMDAL staff members
Assist in the development of data procedures and policies, govern data assets, and improve the quality and access to data across the organization
Analyze and streamline the processes and technology for using data to manage ship maintenance operations, and draw valuable insights from data through data science and business intelligence
Assist in the implementation of industry best practices, selection of enabling tools and technologies, driving innovation, and contributing to new service offerings for our ship maintenance stakeholders
Assist in the development of policies and procedures to ensure corporate data systems information protection, data governance, data quality, and data life cycle management
Qualifications & Requirements:
Master of Science (MS) degree (preferred) or BS/BA (required) in computer science, data science, computational science, or related field
Experience building and leading data management and analytics projects and initiatives
Experience building and leading data management and analytics projects and initiatives for Federal clients
Ability to concisely and convincingly communicate (both verbally and written) with both technical and non-technical stakeholders
Experience using data for descriptive, diagnostic, predictive, and prescriptive analytics
Knowledge of big data technology infrastructure and environments
Proficient in a broad range of data tools and technologies (e.g., Oracle, SQL, SAP IQ, etc.), visualization/analytics tools (e.g., Tableau, Qlik, MicroStrategy, SAP Business Objects, etc.), as well as machine languages (e.g., Python, R/RStudio, Java, C#, SQL, etc.)
Experience in developing machine learning models
Results-driven, creative, and analytical
Strong leadership and ability to work within cross-functional groups
U.S. citizenship
Secret clearance required (with an ability to obtain a Top Secret clearance)

This is a full-time position. NCC offers a competitive compensation packages: salary is commensurate with experience. Benefits include medical, dental, flexible spending, three weeks accrued Paid Time Off (PTO), paid federal holidays, and 401(k) with company match.

Full Description:
About SEIU 775
SEIU 775 is the long-term care workers union, representing more than 45,000 home care and nursing home workers across Washington State and Montana. SEIU 775 is a union committed to improving the lives of workers and their families and to leading the way towards creating a more just and humane society
Position Summary:
The Data Specialist works with internal and external partners to process rosters and financial reports in a timely manner. This position also conducts ongoing audits to ensure external partners are compliant with their Collective Bargaining Agreements (CBA) – contracts between workers and employers – from a data perspective. This position also regularly reviews, resolves, and escalates errors in the database.
Essential Job Functions:
A Process Rosters and Financial Reports from External Partners
First-Level support for External Partners and work with internal partners for when escalated support is needed
Prepare files for import
Record financial information
Match, Create, and Update records in the database
Prepare Data Products for Internal Partners
Monitor Requests for Data Exports
Generate and securely store Data Exports
Create Dashboards
Query, Create, Alter, Remove Tables and Views in SQL Software
Process membership change requests
Audit External Partners’ Processes for Compliance
Audit Database for Accuracy
Member Profiles
Employer Profiles
Operational Processes
Database reconciliation
Review and resolve errors in syncing process
Other duties as assigned
Skills & Abilities:
Data cleaning and preparation
Creating data visualizations
Creating Dashboards and Reports
Writing and Communication for a wide range of tech-literacy levels among stakeholders
Problem Solving
Excellent attention to detail
Be highly collaborative and self-directed.
Have a commitment to our membership and furthering social justice.
Ability to learn from feedback and produce in a fast-paced environment.
Qualifications:
Proficient in MS Excel and MS Word
Proficient in SQL
Familiarity in collaboration with non-tech-minded parties
Experience with cloud-based databases, e.g. Salesforce.com, preferred
Ability to demonstrate experience with leading a project from start to finish, preferred
Familiar with Agile Methodology and Scrums, preferred
Ability to work well and creatively under tight deadlines, in a team environment, preferred
Personal commitment to the mission and goals of SEIU 775 is a requirement of this position (see www.seiu775.org)
Women, non-binary, and people of color are strongly encouraged to apply. Experience working with a labor union, progressive non-profit, community organization, advocacy group, political campaign or elected official is a plus.
Compensation:
This position is full time (40 hours/week). Salary and benefits set by a collectively bargained contract; pay ranges from $28.97 – 35.61 per hour. Benefits include fully employer-paid family health, dental and vision insurance, life insurance, a generous leave package, an ORCA Transit Card, fully employer-paid pension (defined benefit plan), an optional 401(K) plan, and other benefits outlined in the policies of SEIU 775 and the staff union contract.

Full Description:
Lane Powell PC is a law firm synonymous with excellence and innovation. We have 140 years of experience and ambitious goals for the future. At Lane Powell, you will find challenging projects, professional growth opportunities, and an inclusive, entrepreneurial culture.

We are seeking a Financial Data and Reporting Analyst to join our Business Operations and Pricing team. This role works closely with members of the Finance team to enhance reporting on key financial and performance indicators that drive decision making. The role works closely with the Information Technology team to understand and improve systems and business processes related to data. In particular, the role is a liaison between teams around the firm with regard to understanding performance metrics, financial data, budgets and forecasting.

The Business Operations & Pricing team is responsible for processes related to legal performance, realization, pricing and project management at Lane Powell. The team works closely with relationship attorneys, legal teams, firm leadership, and other operations departments to ensure the most effective delivery of legal work at a fair value to our clients. The team supports operational elements of legal product delivery (people, process, technology, and data).

The Financial Data and Reporting Analyst supports the Business Operation & Pricing team’s efforts to support attorney work with data to drive decisions They help query, analyze, and report on performance metrics of all kinds related to both legal teams and organizational performance. They enable and assist with building meaningful data visualization and business intelligence tools. They contribute to continuous improvement of our data standards and integrity.

Job Responsibilities:
Analysis and Reporting
Provide analytical support to operational departments across the firm including financial data analysis and key performance indicator analysis
Contribute in the development, refinement, and implementation of performance monitoring reports including financial statements, pricing analysis and profitability forecasting
Develop dynamic models to conduct data analysis to assist in determining the impact of proposed scenarios
Business Intelligence (BI) and Data Visualization
Collaborate with business and financial analysts across operational departments to ensure data is accessible and structured in a way that enables actionable insight for our leadership, practice teams, and operational teams
Build visualizations and dashboards to allow for easier access and interpretation of data
Identify areas for improvement and recommend solutions for reporting and BI
Promote understanding of law firm performance metrics and help implement improved insight into performance against those metrics
Assist with ideation and creation of templates and tools to help standardize pricing procedures and metrics
Data Stewardship
Contribute to establishing standards that ensure data integrity across our ERP, HRIS, and other source systems
Conduct efforts to bring data in alignment with standards
Champion future efforts to identify potential issues and clean upstream data

Required Skills and Abilities:

Working knowledge of financial ERP systems, related data management and reporting, key financial metrics and financial statements
Working knowledge of BI and data warehouse concepts and terminology
Ability to query and analyze databases and large datasets using SQL or similar languages
Experience building infrastructure for complex reports in Power BI or similar program
Advanced Microsoft Excel skills (ex: data manipulation functions, conditional formatting, charts, PivotTables, Power Query, and VBA)
Detail-oriented person who is passionate about quality and enthusiastic about new technology
Collaborative personality who is able to communicate clearly regarding complex technical topics
Minimum Qualifications
Bachelor’s degree required (Finance, Accounting, Engineering, Information Systems, or other related field preferred)
1-2 years Experience with Financial Planning & Analysis (FP&A) or Audit reporting in a professional setting required
3-5 Years Experience with Data Analysis, dashboarding and reporting
Preferred Qualifications:
Law firm or other professional services experience preferred
Salary Range:
$95,000 - $110,000 annually depending on experience
Hours / Schedule / Location:
40 hours per week / Monday through Friday 8:00 AM – 5:00PM / Greater Seattle Metropolitan Area preferred (reports to Seattle Office)
This is a full-time, exempt position that requires regular and predictable attendance
This position reports directly to the Director of Business Operations and Pricing
This is a hybrid position may require both remote and on-site work. The employee will need to have internet access and a space to work; Lane Powell will provide a laptop and all necessary technology.

Any job offer will be conditional upon successfully completing a pre-employment background screening and reference check

Full Description:
Institutional Effectiveness Analyst

Job ID: 12072
Location: Cascadia College
Full/Part Time: Full Time
Regular/Temporary: Regular

About Us

Cascadia College is seeking highly motivated individuals who are interested in being part of a small yet dynamic community, with a faculty and staff that are dedicated to meeting the needs of our intersectional, diverse students. Cascadia College is committed to creating and supporting an equitable and inclusive faculty, staff, and student population centered on dismantling systemic oppression and historic marginalization. Individual differences are celebrated in a community of learners focused on social justice, diversity, equity and inclusion.
Application Instructions

Institutional Effectiveness Analyst


Priority Consideration: October 19th, 2022, by 11:59pm


ATTENTION CANDIDATES!


In order to submit a complete application and receive full consideration by the Search Committee, please include the following attachments with your online application:

Equity Statement (expected length 800-1,000 words) to include each of the following elements:

A description of a time when you recognized an equity issue. What was the issue? What did you do to make a difference? What did you learn about equity through this experience?

A detailed description of how you are seeking to learn more about equity related issues including but not limited to race, gender, LGBTQ+, disability (ableism), age (ageism), socioeconomic class, and body diversity.

An explanation of how you will contribute to equity at Cascadia (i.e. closing the achievement gap and raising the retention rates amongst historically marginalized students), as well as actively work against the institutionalized norms of oppression against historically marginalized people.

Cover Letter (not to exceed 1,000 words) that specifically addresses how your qualifications and experiences meet or exceed the minimum qualifications, preferred qualifications, and the characteristics of the position.

Resume

Position Overview

Under the general direction of the Director of Institutional Effectiveness, the Institutional Effectiveness Analyst works closely with all levels of college administration to support planning, operations, accountability, and reporting by utilizing skills of data analysis, SQL query development, enterprise data systems, and visual data reporting. Employs a working knowledge of business process analysis and experience in higher education.


As the Institutional Effectiveness Analyst, it is expected that the following qualities will be demonstrated daily: a high degree of understanding and empathy for all students, faculty, staff and visitors, as well as the ability to encourage the inclusion of all voices in decision-making, promoting equity in all areas, and actively working against institutionalized norms of oppression against historically marginalized people.


Employee Type: Full Time Exempt, Permanent

Initial Salary Range: $71,000 - $81,000 (includes 5% King County Premium Pay)

Supervising Position: Director of Institutional Effectiveness
Essential Duties
Respond to a variety of needs in support of the Office of Institutional Effectiveness.

Work with a variety of employees to understand business needs, conduct data analyses, and interpret the results of analysis.

Develop advanced SQL coding to maintain data quality and extract data for analysis.

Create data products by responding to a wide variety of ad hoc requests for analysis.

Takes initiative to research data system issues and solutions.

Complete data analysis for regulatory and funding reporting requirements.

Develop and implement data visualizations and dynamic dashboards.

Develop, maintain, and troubleshoot self-service college data resources.

Document projects including describing procedures and SQL scripts.

Support administration staff on the annual schedule of courses to help ensure accurate schedules and proper coding of course information.

Participate in college-wide committees and meetings as assigned.



Education and Experience:

Minimum Qualifications

A bachelor's degree with study in public administration, social sciences, education, or related field with coursework in quantitative analysis.

A minimum of 3 years' experience as a data analyst.

Demonstrated commitment to equity and inclusion and the ability to support a diverse workplace and educational environment.

Preferred Qualifications

Strong experience working in an institution of higher education.

Technical writing experience including reports and presentations.

Proven success in a collaborative, inclusive, team-oriented environment.

Physical Work Environment:

Semi-Sedentary Work: Involves staying in a stationary position to a significant degree. Jobs are sedentary if moving is required only occasionally and all other sedentary criteria are met.


The College is currently in hybrid operations, with many assignments completed in an online environment during this time. Beginning in Fall Quarter 2022, full-time employees will be expected to be on-campus three (3) days per week with the option to work remotely for the remainder of their working days. Employees will need to provide their own remote workspace and internet access, noting the College will provide technical equipment and support for online work needs. During on-campus operations, this position will perform work in a standard office setting, use standard office equipment and physically attend meetings both on and off campus and requires the ability to communicate in person or through appropriate means.

Full Description:
UW Medicine Faculty Practice Plan Services (FPPS) supports UW Physicians (UWP), a practice group for more than 2,800 physicians and other healthcare professionals associated with UW Medicine. UW Medicine includes Harborview Medical Center, UW Medical Center - Montlake, UW Primary Care Clinics, UW Medical Center - Northwest, the UW School of Medicine, Valley Medical Center, and Airlift Northwest. UWP members also practice at the Seattle Cancer Care Alliance, a partnership of UW Medicine, Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center, and Seattle Children’s Hospital.


FPPS is looking to add a Senior Financial Data Analyst to their Data Analytics team. Under the overall general guidance of the Manager, the Senior Financial Data Analyst will perform analysis, investigate data issues, identify trends, present results, and make recommendations.


JOB LOCATION: Remote from Washington State. Option to work from Columbia Center in Downtown Seattle (701 5th Ave, Seattle) if preferred.


Minimum Qualifications:


REQUIRED:

Bachelor’s Degree in business, mathematics, industrial engineering, health administration, or other related field.

5-7 years of experience in business analysis and requirements definition with a thorough understanding of data analysis and requirements documentation techniques.

2-3 years analytical, auditing or traning experience in a Health Care environment

Experience developing reports using tools such as Business Objects.

OR a combination of experience and/or education


DESIRED:

Master’s degree in Business or Health Administration preferred.

Experience in an academic healthcare environment preferred.

Expertise in Excel preferred.

Experience using healthcare IT technologies, preference for Epic experience, particularly with Epic Resolute PB preferred


RESPONSIBILITIES:


Coordinate with UWP CFO and UW Medicine partners on key cross system including annual budget development and financial analysis including major mission support programs and other joint system program initiatives.


Responsible for UWP fee setting and RVU policies including maintenance and updating of UWP fee schedules.


Supports ad hoc reporting and data analysis work for FPPS Finance and coordinates development and production of standard FPPS reports.


Subject matter expert and key liason for Financial Profee Billing Data and analysis across UW Medicine.


Applicants considered for this position will be required to disclose if they are the subject of any substantiated findings or current investigations related to sexual misconduct at their current employment and past employment. Disclosure is required under Washington state law.

Job Title: associate consultant - d&a bi data visualization (march 2023)
Qualifications:
experience

slalom’s consulting foundations experience is about growing talented, early career professionals into world-class consultants – focused on nurturing our own talent internally, creating more dynamic teams, and building consulting skills. the experience begins with an orientation in your local market, followed by global consulting foundations, where associate consultants from across slalom come together to learn, practice, and develop foundational consulting skills. then you'll continue to grow your skills through a blend of on-the-job training, small group coaching, and independent learning designed to set the stage for a long and fulfilling career. learn more at https://www.slalom.com/consulting-foundations

title: data & analytics associate consultant
cohort start date: march 2023
who you’ll work with
as a modernized technology company, we've never met a technical challenge we didn't like. we enable our clients to learn from their data, create incredible digital experiences, and make the most of new technologies. we blend design, engineering, and analytics expertise to build the future. we surround our technologists with interesting challenges, innovative minds and emerging technologies. the data & analytics practice in seattle is a full-service data practice with competencies across information strategy, modern data architecture, data visualization, and data science.
slalom seattle’s data & analytics practice is looking for motivated early career professionals with a proactive mentality that has a passion for helping organizations solve complex business and technology problems. we are seeking professionals interested in developing skills in the consulting industry. this role will play an integral part in client/project teams and ensure the timely completion of tasks, with guided expansion of discipline breadth and depth.

what you’ll do
contribute to impactful business initiatives in a team setting where each team member brings their own specialized skills
function as a connector between business needs and technology solutions by building relationships with our clients to understand and synthesize their needs
collaboratively participate in agile development projects
embrace a learner mentality, growing your skills at every step of the process while seeking out the best ways to contribute to your project
bring new ideas, passion, and energy to your work
be an advocate and representative for slalom’s values
learn and apply new technical concepts in a project and team setting
develop an understanding of the capabilities and services slalom delivers
build a network within slalom
drive constant improvement in projects, products, and processes by being comfortable escalating and discussing issues when you see them
what you’ll bring
information systems, business analytics, mathematics, data science, engineering, statistics, or quantitative social sciences or related degree with a minimum gpa of 3.0 or higher
experience working with large datasets, sql, and data modeling, as well as an understanding of relational database and data warehousing concepts (snowflake or databricks experience a plus)
working knowledge of data visualization software (power bi, tableau, qlik, quicksight, etc.), coding languages such as r or python, or ability to build models using commercial tools like alteryx, rapidminer, datarobot, azure, google, or aws
ability to drive business insights from data through thoughtful application of best practices and a structured methodology
strong problem-solving and software triage skills with the ability to work cross-functionally in a fast-paced and rapidly changing work environment
strong analytical and interpersonal communication skills
interested in building custom modern digital products, data solutions and cloud platforms? check our opportunities with slalom build.
about us
slalom is a modern consulting firm focused on strategy, technology, and business transformation. in 43 markets around the world, slalom's teams have flexibility to move fast and do what's right. they are backed by regional innovation hubs, a global culture of collaboration, and partnerships with the world's top technology providers. founded in 2001 and headquartered in seattle, slalom has organically grown to over 13,000 employees. slalom has been named one of fortune's 100 best companies to work for five years running and is regularly recognized by employees as a best place to work. learn more at slalom.com.
at slalom, our vision is to create a thriving, inclusive, and diverse global team where people love their work, love working together, and are learning and growing every day. i&de is not just something we do, but rather who we are as a company. our overall i&de strategy is embedded in our greater people strategy to ensure continuity and presence across all our markets and teams.

Full Description:
Slalom Consulting Foundations Experience

Slalom’s Consulting Foundations Experience is about growing talented, early career professionals into world-class consultants – focused on nurturing our own talent internally, creating more dynamic teams, and building consulting skills. The experience begins with an orientation in your local market, followed by Global Consulting Foundations, where Associate Consultants from across Slalom come together to learn, practice, and develop foundational consulting skills. Then you'll continue to grow your skills through a blend of on-the-job training, small group coaching, and independent learning designed to set the stage for a long and fulfilling career. Learn more at https://www.slalom.com/consulting-foundations

TITLE: Data & Analytics Associate Consultant
Cohort Start Date: March 2023
Who You’ll Work With
As a modernized technology company, we've never met a technical challenge we didn't like. We enable our clients to learn from their data, create incredible digital experiences, and make the most of new technologies. We blend design, engineering, and analytics expertise to build the future. We surround our technologists with interesting challenges, innovative minds and emerging technologies. The Data & Analytics practice in Seattle is a full-service data practice with competencies across information strategy, modern data architecture, data visualization, and data science.
Slalom Seattle’s Data & Analytics practice is looking for motivated early career professionals with a proactive mentality that has a passion for helping organizations solve complex business and technology problems. We are seeking professionals interested in developing skills in the consulting industry. This role will play an integral part in client/project teams and ensure the timely completion of tasks, with guided expansion of discipline breadth and depth.

What You’ll Do
Contribute to impactful business initiatives in a team setting where each team member brings their own specialized skills
Function as a connector between business needs and technology solutions by building relationships with our clients to understand and synthesize their needs
Collaboratively participate in agile development projects
Embrace a learner mentality, growing your skills at every step of the process while seeking out the best ways to contribute to your project
Bring new ideas, passion, and energy to your work
Be an advocate and representative for Slalom’s values
Learn and apply new technical concepts in a project and team setting
Develop an understanding of the capabilities and services Slalom delivers
Build a network within Slalom
Drive constant improvement in projects, products, and processes by being comfortable escalating and discussing issues when you see them
What You’ll Bring
Information Systems, Business Analytics, Mathematics, Data Science, Engineering, Statistics, or Quantitative Social Sciences or related degree with a minimum GPA of 3.0 or higher
Experience working with large datasets, SQL, and data modeling, as well as an understanding of relational database and data warehousing concepts (Snowflake or Databricks experience a plus)
Working knowledge of data visualization software (Power BI, Tableau, Qlik, Quicksight, etc.), coding languages such as R or Python, or ability to build models using commercial tools like Alteryx, RapidMiner, DataRobot, Azure, Google, or AWS
Ability to drive business insights from data through thoughtful application of best practices and a structured methodology
Strong problem-solving and software triage skills with the ability to work cross-functionally in a fast-paced and rapidly changing work environment
Strong analytical and interpersonal communication skills
Interested in building custom modern digital products, data solutions and cloud platforms? Check our opportunities with Slalom Build.
About Us
Slalom is a modern consulting firm focused on strategy, technology, and business transformation. In 43 markets around the world, Slalom's teams have flexibility to move fast and do what's right. They are backed by regional innovation hubs, a global culture of collaboration, and partnerships with the world's top technology providers. Founded in 2001 and headquartered in Seattle, Slalom has organically grown to over 13,000 employees. Slalom has been named one of Fortune's 100 Best Companies to Work For five years running and is regularly recognized by employees as a best place to work. Learn more at slalom.com.
At Slalom, our vision is to create a thriving, inclusive, and diverse global team where people love their work, love working together, and are learning and growing every day. I&DE is not just something we do, but rather who we are as a company. Our overall I&DE strategy is embedded in our greater People Strategy to ensure continuity and presence across all our markets and teams.
We lead with inclusion and believe that all our employees should feel understood, included, connected and safe. We’re committed to a diverse workforce at all levels, and we view diversity broadly (gender, race/ethnicity, disability, background, geography, thinking, working styles, etc.). Equity is our responsibility and our North Star.
Learn more about our commitments to ID&E as well as our Corporate Social Responsibility commitments at Slalom.com.

Full Description:
The Business Analyst is responsible for reviewing, prioritizing, modifying and recommending business requirements applied to our databases and systems under the direct oversight of the Business Process Director. In addition, this role will pinpoint how Exotic can leverage its strengths and improve its weaknesses through various business process improvements and through the use of technology or software. This role works closely with the programming team to test the solution, record and track technical issues and implement any needed changes.

Duties and Responsibilities:

Review, prioritize and propose business process improvements across all departments within the organization.

Recommend solutions that are right sized, robust, stable and designed for the long term. Must be able to see big picture impacts on other systems and assess risk.

Partner with business/user representatives to understand the customer processes and user needs.

Develop business processes using task flow analysis and work flow analysis

 Research, analyze, and present the most relevant information about the project

 Know when to recommend a project be delayed or terminated

Able to differentiate between desired and required user needs

Use strong analytical reasoning to understand end user’s requirements to create an operational application.

Acquire deep working knowledge of Exotic’s business systems and bring efficient and effective changes for better performance.

Understand the technical designs and specifications.

Communicate effectively with internal teams and external clients to understand their needs and deliver both functional requirements and formal, documented business processes.

Act as project manager for cross functional team initiatives.


Required Skills

Required Experience
The ideal candidate will have excellent written, oral, organization, project management, presentation and interpersonal communication skills. Because business analysts must interact with executives, users and technical staff, networking and team building skills are preferred. Business analysts should also have the ability to train, lead and mentor other analysts.

Time and project management and prioritization skills a must. Demonstrated success in leading projects to close on time, within budget and within scope. Able to understand the customer’s needs and position a solution which best addresses all of the customer’s needs.

Strong analytic and technical skills including writing functional and technical requirements. Database design, software design and testing methodology a must.

Strong problem solving and decision making skills.

Full Description:
Position Description
Seattle Human Resources endeavors to promote an equitable and engaging work environment so employees can do their best work and make a difference for the people and communities we serve. The Department focuses on providing high quality services to all City employees and departments and works collaboratively with department leaders to align policies, practices, and programs citywide to fulfill the vision of workforce equity and excellence.
As part of this mission, the Fire and Police Exams Unit is responsible for developing and administering merit-based, entry-level, and promotional exams under the direction of the Public Safety Civil Service Commission (PSCSC) and on behalf of the Seattle Police and Fire Departments to establish eligibility lists to fill entry-level, lateral, and promotional positions. We strive to administer exams that are equitable, compliant, and transparent. To support these goals, we are looking for a Fire and Police Exams Analyst who will provide program coordination, research and analysis, and support a high volume of exams administered on behalf of the Fire and Police Departments. This position will also increase the unit’s capacity to administer entry and lateral police officer exam administrations.
This position will give you the opportunity to work with a diverse team that centers equity, learning, transparency, and continuous improvement to serve our uniformed employees and the broader community. In this role, you will support the administration of entry and promotional exams, research best practices, analyze data, provide customer service to candidates and partner departments, manage dashboards, budgets, contracts, and records, coordinate public disclosure requests, and provide general logistical support. In addition, you will have the opportunity to regularly utilize your problem-solving and organizational skills to improve exam administration for both the Fire and Police Departments, ultimately making our community a safer and more equitable place by contributing to hiring and promotional processes.
Job Responsibilities
In this role:
You will be successful if you feel passionate about:
Improving administrative processes and identifying opportunities that make a significant impact
Providing exceptional and welcoming customer service to fire and police exam candidates
Solving complex problems creatively and efficiently
Building and maintaining positive team relationships
Maintaining the utmost level of security and confidentiality
Identifying and undoing inequities in examination processes
Utilizing your organizational skills for seamless project coordination and records management
 Your effectiveness will depend on your ability to:
Communicate effectively, both orally and in writing
Apply critical thinking and problem-solving in a fast-paced environment
Research and analyze exam administration decisions, past practices, and best practices, providing recommendations and revisions as necessary
Partner tactfully, courteously, and effectively with a variety of people, members of the Seattle Police and Fire Departments, as well as the Public Safety Civil Service Commission and consultants and other industry subject matter experts
Support Senior Analysts by facilitating exam development committee meetings, administering protest periods, and fielding stakeholder communications
Supporting the Fire & Police Exams Unit in testifying and defending work before the PSCSC
 You will feel prepared if you have experience in:
Supporting and administering employment-related examinations (written, oral board, working tests, practical exams, certifications, etcetera), particularly public safety or apprenticeship exams
Researching and interpreting rules, regulations, contracts, and policies and procedures
Communicating technical exam-related concepts to non-technical audiences
Coordinating exam logistics, such as booking hotels, event spaces, airfare, and shuttles
Applying your advanced skills in Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and Outlook
Conducting statistical reports and creating data dashboards
Processing and monitoring contracts and receipts
Providing instructions and assistance to large groups of people
Industrial or Organizational Psychology and Personnel Selection
Qualifications
In addition to the ability to perform the tasks described above, you will need to possess the below required qualifications:
A Bachelor’s Degree in Human Resource Management, Business or Public Administration, Social Sciences, or a related field
Two years in personnel selection assessments (preferably for Civil Service positions), public-sector exams, or performing other human resources-related tasks, or a related field
OR
An Associate Degree in Human Resource Management, Business or Public Administration, Social Sciences, or a related field
Three years in personnel selection assessments (preferably for Civil Service positions), public-sector exams, or performing other human resources-related tasks, or a related field
OR
Four years in personnel selection assessments (preferably for Civil Service positions), public-sector exams, or performing other human resources-related tasks, or a related field
Additional Information
This position is classified a Personnel Analyst and requires the ability to lift 30 pounds and work paid overtime, evenings, and weekends.
The first round of interviews for this position are tentatively scheduled for Thursday, January 12 and Friday, January 13, with the second round taking place on Thursday, January 19, 2023.
Applicants must successfully pass a background check, which will be conducted in accordance with Seattle’s Fair Chance Employment Ordinance, SMC 14.17. Applicants will be given a chance to explain or correct background information and provide verifiable information of good conduct and rehabilitation.
The City of Seattle recognizes every City employee must play a role in ending institutional and structural racism. Our culture is the result of our behavior, our personal commitments, and the ways we courageously share our perspectives and encourage others to do the same. To cultivate an antiracist culture, we seek employees who will engage in the Race and Social Justice Initiative by working to dismantle racist policies and procedures, unlearn the way things have always been done, and provide equitable processes and services.
COVID 19 Vaccination Mandate - City of Seattle employees are required to be fully vaccinated against COVID-19. If hired, you will be required to submit proof of vaccination prior to your employment start date. People are considered fully vaccinated two weeks after their second dose in a two-dose series or two weeks after a single-dose vaccine. Employees may make requests for a reasonable accommodation based on a medical disability or for sincerely held religious beliefs. Philosophical, political, scientific, or sociological objections to vaccination will not be considered for an exemption or accommodation.
APPLICATION PROCESS:
To be considered for this position, please submit your complete application, resume, and cover letter to https://www.governmentjobs.com/careers/seattle no later than 4:00pm Pacific Time on Tuesday, January 3, 2023. In your 1-page cover letter, please explain your interest in this position and identify specifically how the combination of your knowledge, skills, and interests align with our business needs and will contribute to your success in this role. This position is open to all candidates that meet the minimum qualifications. The City of Seattle values diverse perspectives and life experiences. Applicants will be considered regardless of race, color, creed, national origin, ancestry, sex, marital status, disability, religious or political affiliation, age, sexual orientation, medical condition, or pregnancy. The City of Seattle encourages people of all backgrounds to apply, including people of color, immigrants, refugees, women, LGBTQ, people with disabilities, veterans, and those with diverse life experiences. If you have questions, please contact Lindsey King at Lindsey.King@seattle.gov.

Full Description:
Junior Data Strategy Analyst (JDSA)
In support of the Naval Sea Systems Command (NAVSEA) and the Shipboard Maintenance Performance Group (SMPG), the JDSA will help bring cutting edge data analytics to the Navy fleet. Positions are located in Norfolk, VA, and Bremerton, WA.

Roles & Responsibilities:
The Junior Data Strategy Analyst reports to and assist the program’s Senior Data Strategy Analyst (SDSA) in all activities required to modernize the management and analysis of data within the Ship Maintenance Community. The roles and responsibilities of the JDSA will be similar in nature to those of the SDSA but at a level commensurate with the knowledge and experience of the candidate. These include:
Assist in the stand-up (both technical and functional) of the Data Analytics Lab located at SMPG offices, recommend software/hardware analytics and data management toolsets, and recommend functional responsibilities for the other SMDAL staff members
Assist in the development of data procedures and policies, govern data assets, and improve the quality and access to data across the organization
Analyze and streamline the processes and technology for using data to manage ship maintenance operations, and draw valuable insights from data through data science and business intelligence
Assist in the implementation of industry best practices, selection of enabling tools and technologies, driving innovation, and contributing to new service offerings for our ship maintenance stakeholders
Assist in the development of policies and procedures to ensure corporate data systems information protection, data governance, data quality, and data life cycle management
Qualifications & Requirements:
Master of Science (MS) degree (preferred) or BS/BA (required) in computer science, data science, computational science, or related field
Experience building and leading data management and analytics projects and initiatives
Experience building and leading data management and analytics projects and initiatives for Federal clients
Ability to concisely and convincingly communicate (both verbally and written) with both technical and non-technical stakeholders
Experience using data for descriptive, diagnostic, predictive, and prescriptive analytics
Knowledge of big data technology infrastructure and environments
Proficient in a broad range of data tools and technologies (e.g., Oracle, SQL, SAP IQ, etc.), visualization/analytics tools (e.g., Tableau, Qlik, MicroStrategy, SAP Business Objects, etc.), as well as machine languages (e.g., Python, R/RStudio, Java, C#, SQL, etc.)
Experience in developing machine learning models
Results-driven, creative, and analytical
Strong leadership and ability to work within cross-functional groups
U.S. citizenship
Secret clearance required (with an ability to obtain a Top Secret clearance)

Full Description: About UsCascade Energy, founded in 1993, is an employee-owned consulting firm specializing in industrial energy efficiency. Our mission is to improve the energy efficiency of the most energy-intensive sector of our economy - industrial. Today, we are a fast-growing team of 200+ and our work reaches throughout North America, with clients ranging in size from small to Fortune 500 companies. We foster and value a culture of equals, initiative, and ownership.Why work at Cascade?At Cascade, our teams reflect our company values, which are: do the right thing; put others first; seek shared success; learn constantly; and be industrious. You’ll likely find this opportunity attractive if you love to learn new things, have a growth mindset, and want to join a team that puts our values at the heart of decision making and is constantly striving towards “better.”In alignment with our values and doing better, Cascade Energy is committed to improving the state of diversity, equity, inclusion, and accessibility (DEIA) within our organization and the communities in which we work and live. We celebrate and value diversity as a source for different perspectives, increased creativity, higher innovation, and faster problem solving and are committed to providing an environment of mutual respect, free of discrimination and harassment. Learn more about DEIA at Cascade by visiting cascadeenergy.com/deiaCascade promotes a healthy work-life balance and appreciates employee contribution in all areas. We walk the talk about our commitment to learning constantly, with a focus on the ongoing development of every team member, and a tuition reimbursement program. Cascade is a strong supporter of flexible working arrangements, and offers role-dependent options for remote, hybrid, and in-office work.About This OpportunityWe are seeking a Program Analyst (Business Analyst). Cascade Energy is the third-party contractor responsible for the delivery of the Bonneville Power Administration’s (BPA) Energy Smart Industrial (ESI) program. ESI is a multifaceted, large-scale industrial efficiency program offered through BPA’s utility customers in the Pacific Northwest.The Program Analyst applies data and organizational skills to provide ongoing operational, administrative, strategic, and logistical reporting support to ESI’s Strategic Energy Management (SEM) program. This is a dynamic role with duties encompassing a range of tasks and autonomous projects in support of ESI’s goals and KPIs. The Program Analyst is highly organized, enjoys using data to develop stories or approaches that point to new insights, tools, Key Performance Indicators (KPI’s) and reporting to advance operational performance, efficiency, and decision-making. The Program Analyst also enjoys exercising a high level of proficiency in key software programs, such as SharePoint Online, PowerSuite, and Excel with enthusiasm for developing additional system knowledge as required.What You Will Be Doing:Duties include but are not limited to the following:Review the program contract to fully understand tracking and reporting requirements, revenue sources, and customer expectations.Attend key meetings alongside the Energy Management Program Manager.Complete projects and special assignments related to program operations by establishing objectives, determining priorities, managing time, gaining cooperation and input from others, monitoring progress, problem-solving, and ensuring continuous improvement.Creation, auditing, and ongoing management of program reports on a weekly, monthly, and quarterly basis. May include use of program-specific software programs (SharePoint, Ajera, Asana, Energy Sensei, Power BI, and others) to support team tracking and reporting needs.Maintain systems and reporting for the collection, data visualization and analysis of key delivery KPI’s (savings data, pipeline, strategic advisor, budget/cost analysis trends, billable targets, and benchmarking).Collect, aggregate, and explore data, using it to draw conclusions and illustrate opportunities for operational improvements and consistency.Assist the Energy Management team with high level project and program support, including assembling sophisticated reports, analyzing large data sets, and extrapolating appropriate materials for the team.Assist with the development, production, maintenance, and distribution of marketing materials and report templates.Reasonable accommodations will be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions of the job.This is a full-time, exempt position. The position may be fully remote, in-office, or a hybrid. Preference will be given to applicants near one of the following Cascade offices: Portland, Walla Walla, Issaquah, or Boise.Minimal travel is anticipated for this role. Approximately 5%QualificationsApplicants for this role are required to have:Bachelor’s degree in business, economics, finance, engineering, behavioral science, or equivalent relative technical backgroundAt least 2-4 years of experience in a relevant role, with a track record of escalating responsibility over timeExperience managing many customers and programs across multiple locations.Ability to understand and foster the customer relationship and successfully weave clients’ needs (and contractual requirements) into KPIs.Strong verbal and written communication skills, with an affinity for adapting conversational content into data for analysis and an ability to proofread with attention to grammar, style, and technical detail.Ability to make independent judgements or ask for assistance in ambiguous circumstances.Ability to apply critical thinking skills to address situations based on all available facts and information.Exceptionally detail-oriented with a high degree of accuracy.Ability to troubleshoot systems (e.g., SharePoint databases and workflows) while helping internal and external customers use and navigate the site.Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, deadline-driven environment, achieving satisfaction from meeting tight deadlines and displaying strength in multitasking.Proficient with SharePoint Online and Microsoft Power Platform suite (Power BI), with expert-level Excel and Word skills.A successful candidate should also demonstrate these preferred characteristics and/or skills:Experience in the energy industry or demand-side management programs preferred but not required.For candidates whose experience may not align perfectly with all these preferred skills but can see themselves adding value in this role, we encourage you to still apply. Full Description:
Job Title: Foundational Community Supports Data Analyst
Days Off: Saturday, Sunday
Pay Range: $63,355.50 - $71,682 annually
Shift: Office Day
Location: Remote (Washington State only)
Insurance Benefits: Dental, Life, Long-term Disability, Medical (no premiums/payroll deductions for employee coverage)
Other Benefits: Employee Assistance Program (EAP), Flexible Spending Account (FSA), ORCA card subsidy, Paid Time Off (34 days per year), Retirement Plan
About DESC
DESC (Downtown Emergency Service Center) is a nonprofit organization working to help people with the complex needs of homelessness, substance use disorders, and serious mental illness achieve their highest potential for health and well-being through comprehensive services, treatment, and housing. Our vision is a community where no person is abandoned, ignored, or experiencing homelessness.
As the region's leading provider of services to multiply disabled adults who have experienced chronic homelessness, DESC serves almost 2,000 people each day. Our integrated service model is designed to help people secure and maintain appropriate, safe and affordable housing. DESC is recognized nationally and regionally as an innovator in developing solutions to homelessness.
JOB DEFINITION:

The Foundational Community Supports (FCS) Data Analyst is a member of a multi-disciplinary team that will support DESC’s mission by using data queries, creating reports, and providing administrative services for programs leveraging the 1115 Waiver. Considerable attention and skills are needed in the areas of data analytics, presentation, and problem solving. The FCS Data Analyst will work closely with the Senior Manager of Policy and Program Analytics to ensure programs leveraging Medicaid Waiver dollars are complying with all applicable laws, regulations and contract requirements.

MAJOR DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:

Use data sources to perform validation and quality control checks to track performance and compliance in identified areas.

Assist with the collection of data and analysis requested by 1115 Waiver Programs.

Use SQL to access data and write reports to query information from databases.

Assist staff with client enrollment and communication of benefit status information.

Identify and create processes improvements and workflow automation to increase program performance.

Collaborate with the Housing and Quality and Information Management Departments and other DESC partners to scope, design, and validate recurring and ad hoc reports.

Document project details and maintain report specifications that clearly describe how the report works and work with end-users to ensure usage and usability.

Serves as a subject matter expert for department managers on documentation standards that comply with regulatory requirements.

Research, audit, and investigate proper payment of claims.

Assist in various quality assurance activities, including but not limited to fidelity audits.

Serve as a liaison between Amerigroup, King County, HCA, and DESC on all administrative matters.

Comply with all agency policies and procedures, relevant Washington Administrative Code, RCWs, and HIPAA Privacy Rules.

Attend and participate in relevant team meetings, agency sponsored trainings and all-staff meetings.

Other duties as assigned.
MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS:

Bachelor’s or associate’s degree, or 2 years of highly relevant paid work experience and formal training in data analytics and financial accounting to demonstrate an ability to successfully perform the job.

Strong computer skills, including using word processors, analyzing Excel spreadsheets, and writing SQL queries.

Strong oral and written communication skills and ability to work effectively with staff from various backgrounds and disciplines.

Ability to organize and coordinate work efficiently; prioritize workload, work under pressure with tight timelines and changing priorities.

Ability to work independently with a minimum of supervision, and act on own initiative, within agency procedural guidelines.

Initiative and creativity in problem solving and system development.

Willingness to be flexible and work cooperatively with co-workers to accomplish all responsibilities of the team.

Subscribe to philosophy of cooperation and continuity across programs, and of consideration and respect for clients.

Experience working with homeless, mentally ill and/or substance abusers desired.

Appropriate safeguarding and handling of confidential and proprietary information.
PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS:

Bachelor's degree in computer science, accounting, data analytics, healthcare management, analytical science, engineering, or related field or equivalent experience: advanced degree a plus.

4 years highly relevant paid work experience.

Experience working in administration/coordination in a human services, housing or health care setting.

Experience with a formal programming language, such as Python, R, or PHP
PHYSICAL DEMANDS
The physical demands described here are representative of those that must be met by an employee to successfully perform the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions. While performing the duties of this job, the employee will be required sit for long periods of time, communicate with other employees by talking and hearing, and to operate computer systems. Specific vision abilities required by the job include close vision, distance vision, color vision, peripheral vision, depth perception, and the ability to adjust focus.

EQUAL OPPORTUNITY EMPLOYER

The Agency will not discriminate against any employee or applicant for employment on the basis of race, creed, color, sex, gender, sexual orientation, age, national origin, marital status, or the presence of any sensory, mental or physical disability in any employment practice, unless based on a bona fide occupational qualification.
