Full Description:
Company Description
You may know us as FIJI Water, POM Wonderful, Justin Wine, Teleflora and Halos Citrus, but we’re all Wonderful – and we have a great opportunity for a Business Systems Analyst (Supply Chain Planning).
The Business Systems Analyst will plan, implement and support system solutions in demand management, sales & operations planning, supply planning, production scheduling etc. using various Oracle value chain planning products (Oracle Fusion Planning modules, Demantra etc) and other planning products.
Are you willing to relocate to Delano, CA? This position will be based at our Delano office and working a hybrid schedule with 3 days per week in the office.Visa & relocation assistance provided

Job Description
Solution Development:
Consult with business unit management to identify business needs, understand current operational procedures and problems in Demand Management, Supply planning, sales & operations planning and other planning areas.
Define solutions in Oracle Fusion SCP, Oracle Demantra/VCP/EBS or other implemented planning products for various business needs, communicate in clear terms to business users the solution options and assist them in decision making.
Create and update solution and process documents.
Create requirements, functional specifications, unit and integrated test scenario documents and other relevant artifacts necessary for implementation of IT solution.
Project and Task Management:
Create and maintain project plans to implement approved IT projects.
Direct partner and internal resources on project tasks.
Monitor project activities per the plan and communicate status to key stakeholders.
Communicate and coordinate development from geographically dispersed teams.
Operational Support:
Identify, evaluate, and resolve day-to-day support issues in area of Oracle fusion SCP, planning applications and Demantra.
Coordinate with offshore resources on successful resolution of support tickets.
Create / update end user training documents and guides.
Provide hands-on training to end users on various aspects of applications.

Qualifications

Minimum of 6-8 years of experience in implementing enterprise applications with at least 4 years in implementing Oracle Value Chain Planning products (ex ASCP); Demantra modules or one of the advanced planning applications.
Should have performed at least 3 full life cycle implementations of planning modules in recent releases.
Strong functional knowledge in core SCP products and integration to Oracle Fusion R13 / EBS R12.
Experience working in a multi divisional environment with one VCP platform and multiple executions systems (Oracle fusion / ERP) is preferred.

Job Description
The Data Analyst III will be a senior member of the Supply Chain Insights & Analytics team, owning the collection and delivery of data and insights for Nordstrom’s Supply Chain Organization. The Data Analyst III will provide ongoing data support, performance analysis and storytelling, which will lead to value creation and enable the next cycle of growth within Nordstrom – supporting a reliable and efficient Supply Chain model to optimize how we serve customers and stores across the Nordstrom businesses.
A day in the life…
Own “the truth” and governance in data and process including the intake, management, automation, and integrity of data utilized by the Supply Chain organization and its business partners
Champion the data needs and priorities of the Supply Chain Insights & Analytics team, coordinating with key data/business partners across the Nordstrom organization including Product Management, Data Science, Nordstrom Technology, Finance, and Merchandizing

Support Supply Chain business analysts in the development of modernized reporting and effective analysis, creating compelling narratives and storytelling through data
Support the analysis and diagnosis of end-to-end supply chain performance and provide actionable guidance to improve results

You own this if you have…

Full Description:
This is a 100% fully remote role. Work virtually from anywhere in the Continental U.S.

Varis is a well-funded and fast-growing technology startup that focuses on digital commerce software-as-a-service and procurement and is owned by The ODP Corporation (NASDAQ: ODP). We are innovation driven, customer centric, and ready to transform eProcurement and business-to-business (B2B) Marketplaces. Our culture is focused on a bold vision, launching the simplest (yet still valuable) solutions to learn, then either failing or scaling fast as we iterate towards our product goals.

Joining us now is a ground-floor opportunity to shape our limitless future. You will see and feel the direct impact of your work, be surrounded by passionate people, learn how to be an entrepreneur, and be at the center of a highly dynamic business model with tremendous individual and collective potential.
Apply quickly by emailing your resume here: data_business_analyst__8c2d867b5us@iris.greenhouse.io

What You'll Do

We are looking for a Senior Business Analyst for our Business Planning and Strategy team. As a Senior Business Analyst, you will work closely with Product Managers, Program Managers, Business Operation Managers, and Software Developers to generate actionable insights that guide operational excellence and product development.
Your work will have a direct impact on decision-making and strategy for our team. You will support this initiative by developing business metrics and reports, analyzing current processes to provide solutions for improvements, and helping executive leaders make key business decisions.
The successful candidate will communicate effectively across teams and levels while balancing the needs and requirements of internal and external customers. We seek an individual who is motivated by a fast-paced and highly entrepreneurial environment.

Key Responsibilities:

Own the design, development, and maintenance of ongoing and ad-hoc metrics, reports, and analyses, that drive key business decisions
Gather and analyze data for potential business expansion
Prepare and present results of analysis and reports along with their relative impact(s) to the business to all levels of management.
Create reports, dashboards, and visualizations with business intelligence tools (excel, visualization tools, and SQL), to understand business performance
Participate in strategic & tactical planning discussions
Coordinate with different departmental teams to produce better business outcomes
Collaborate with the product manager on roadmap planning and prioritization

What You'll Need

Bachelor's degree in Business, Engineering, Statistics, Computer Science, Mathematics, Supply Chain or a related field
7+ years in corporate operations.
3+ years of relevant experience in a business analyst/data analyst/statistical analyst role.
2+ years of experience with business metrics reporting for corporate functions like finance/sales etc.
Experience in supporting C-level is a big bonus.
Excel modeling.
Experience in developing requirements and formulating business metrics for reporting, familiarity with data visualization tools like PowerBI and Tableau.
SQL proficiency, can write basic SQL queries
Knowledge of DAX is desirable
Excellent communication (verbal and written) and interpersonal skills with both technical and business audiences.
Demonstrated ability to manage multiple projects, prioritization, planning, and task delegation.
Strong critical thinking and problem-solving.
Ability to display complex data in a simple, intuitive format and to present findings in a clear and concise manner
Ability to collaborate and communicate effectively with Sales, Finance and Executive teams
Domain knowledge of eCommerce/indirect procurement/Saas is desirable
Proven ability to work independently in a fast-paced environment.

The above statements are intended to describe the general nature and level of work being performed by associates assigned to this classification and are not intended to be a complete list of all required responsibilities and skills. Other duties and special projects may be assigned per business needs. Job descriptions are subject to change at any time with or without notice.

Full Description:
This is an environment unlike anything in the high-tech world and the secret of Costco’s success is its culture. The value Costco puts on its employees is well documented in articles from a variety of publishers including Bloomberg and Forbes. Our employees and our members come FIRST. Costco is well known for its generosity and community service and has won many awards for its philanthropy. The company joins with its employees to take an active role in volunteering by sponsoring many opportunities to help others. In 2021, Costco contributed over $58 million to organizations such as United Way and Children's Miracle Network Hospitals.

Costco IT is responsible for the technical future of Costco Wholesale, the third largest retailer in the world with wholesale operations in fourteen countries. Despite our size and explosive international expansion, we continue to provide a family, employee centric atmosphere in which our employees thrive and succeed. As proof, Costco ranks seventh in Forbes “World’s Best Employers”.

The Asset Management team is looking for an experienced business operation analyst with a passion for problem-solving looking for an opportunity to create an impact. A high-energy, detail-oriented team player with exemplary communication skills and an innate drive to meet department goals.

The Asset Management team, focuses on managing the business operational movement of IT assets and consumables for the full lifecycle from receipt through disposal including managing the relationships between hardware and software for Costco locations. Our team is focused on maintaining software compliance, identifying savings opportunities, and providing visibility of our license position to all business stakeholders. We are looking for a collaborative analyst in a non-technical role to help us elevate our IT processes and lead initiatives to make positive impacts across Costco IT.

You will be a part of a passionate business team that is agile and collaborative, working together to develop and maintain an excellent Asset Management program. We are serious about our work but our team knows how to have fun while engaged in this crucial service! Come join our team as we continue to shape and evolve ITAM at Costco!
If you want to be a part of one of the worldwide BEST companies “to work for”, simply apply and let your career be reimagined.

ROLE

 Conducts reviews and analysis of software asset data, identifying data integrity issues and root causes of anomalies. Data sets vary from single-system to larger exports that require comparative analysis.

 Provides resolution of discrepancies between pulled inventory data and CARTS data. This may involve detailed research within Flexera, CARTS, and other source data (BigFix, SCCM).

 Supports all efforts to expand software visibility of total footprint in software asset management tool. Primarily focused on how to get more information in-tool and ensuring all included info is accurate and complete.

 Learns, understands, and provides subject matter expertise in proper asset management policies and procedures across purchasing, contracts, supplier management, and business owner teams; ensures software installation is reflective of any hardware retirements and that new hardware is correctly set up in alignment with Software Asset Management (SAM) requirements.
 Creates, maintains process, and references documentations. This may include policy descriptions, reference lists, process flows, or historical logs of resolved issues.

 Initiates cross-collaboration with internal and supplier teams and supports team members in problem resolution efforts.
 Supports the development of ITAM Control Book and related policies. This may include maintenance of existing content, creation of new content, or contributing to process ideation of updates where needed.

 Supports new SAM publisher candidate onboarding.

 Identifies opportunities for streamlining, increasing effectiveness through continuous process improvement and in implementing best practice solutions.

REQUIRED

 2+ years’ of experience in asset management with knowledge of industry best practices; or equivalent inventory/materials management experience.

 Strong understanding of hardware and software asset life cycles and supply chain methods and processes; from purchase through disposal.

 Experience utilizing Excel to analyze data sets is preferred; including experience with pivot tables and formulas, and the ability to compare different data sets.

 Analytical, detail-oriented and demonstrates the ability to research and problem-solve effectively. Able to compare and review data for inconsistencies, can communicate and understand root causes, and takes lead on resolution; can engage other teams as necessary.

 Must possess a positive attitude, ability to work independently, and be self-motivated to take initiative with a strong sense of urgency and ownership.

 Must possess the ability to communicate effectively, both written and verbal, with suppliers, cross-functional teams, and with all organizational levels of Costco.

 Previous experience successfully managing multiple projects and tasks; excellent organizational skills and the ability to prioritize across competing priorities and deadlines.

 Willingness to take direction and coaching from management and peers; excellent and positive team interaction.

 Must be flexible and adaptable to changes.

 Able to work O/T as necessary.

Recommended
 Experience with ServiceNow (“CARTS”) is preferred, especially in the hardware asset management modules.

 IT Asset Management certification (ex. CHAMP, CSAM, CITAM, or equivalent).
 Good understanding of Costco Business operations is preferred; or other knowledge of the structure of a large organization with equipment at multiple locations.

 Experience with discovery tool data from SCCM, BigFix, or ServiceNow Discovery.

 Experience with G-Suite (GoogleDocs, GoogleSheets, etc.).

Full Description:
JAMCO AMERICA, INC.

Job Title: Business Intelligence Analyst
Department: Information Systems
Reports To: Information Systems Supervisor
FLSA Status: Non-Exempt
Summary
The Business Intelligence (BI) Analyst will be responsible for designing, developing, and deploying reporting and dashboard BI solutions. They will work with business stakeholders and end-users to understand business requirements and translate them into functional reports and dashboards. The BI Analyst will also be responsible for maintaining and supporting existing reports, dashboards, and current BI environment.
Essential Duties and Responsibilities include the following with other duties as assigned:
Design, develop, and publish reports and dashboards using BI solutions.
Work with business stakeholders and end-users to understand business requirements and translate them into functional reports and dashboards.
Maintain and support existing reports and dashboards.
Manage data gateways and scheduled refreshes.
Coordinate with Applications Specialists to access data required for reporting.
Respond to general questions and inquiries about BI solutions.
Share and define insights, best practices, and standards that can be applied to improve system, platform, and/or report development.
Supervisory Responsibility
This job has no supervisory responsibilities.
Requirements
Education and Experience:
BS in Computer Science or related field or equivalent work experience.
1+ years of experience developing reports and dashboards using Microsoft Power BI.
Strong understanding of data analysis, data modeling, and data visualization.
Fluency in Power Query M, DAX, Python, and SQL.
Familiarity with Epicor ERP a plus.
Able to properly understand the business requirements and develop data models to meet customer's needs.
Excellent analytical skills.
Ability to think outside the box to find creative solutions to problems.
Strong independent work ethic.
Ability to multitask in a changing environment.
Clear, concise, organized, and professional communication skills.
Qualifications
To perform this job successfully, an individual must be able to perform each essential duty to the established department standards (i.e. meet published metrics). The requirements listed below are representative of the knowledge, skill and/or ability required. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.
All external hiring is contingent upon the successful completion of a pre-employment drug screen and a criminal background check.
Responsibility
The scope of work performed requires coordination and integration of tasks among departmental employees and may involve responsibility for ongoing contacts, employees, and vendors. Translate business needs to technical specifications. Will need to be able to design, build and deploy BI solutions. Conduct unit testing and troubleshooting. Evaluate and improve existing BI solutions. Create visualizations and reports for requested need.
Language Skill
Ability to read, analyze, and interpret general business periodicals, professional journals, technical procedures, or governmental regulations. Ability to write reports, business correspondence, and procedure manuals. Ability to effectively present information and respond to questions from groups of managers, clients, customers, and the general public.
Mathematical
Ability to calculate figures and amounts such as discounts, interest, commissions, proportions, percentages, area, circumference, and volume. Ability to apply concepts of basic algebra and geometry.
Reasoning Ability
Ability to solve practical problems and deal with a variety of concrete variables in situations where only limited standardization exists. Ability to interpret a variety of instructions furnished in written, oral, diagram, or schedule form.
Customer Orientation
Must demonstrate concern and take actions to meet requirements and high standards of quality of both internal and external customers. Must display courtesy and sensitivity. Manage difficult situations. Meet commitments. Respond promptly to customer needs. Solicit customer feedback to improve service.
Physical Demands
While performing the duties of this job, the employee is frequently required to stand, walk, sit, talk, and hear.
Work Environment:
The work environment characteristics described here are representative of those an employee encounters while performing the essential functions of this job. Reasonable accommodations may be made to enable individuals with disabilities to perform the essential functions.
The noise level in the work environment is usually quiet.
